<refpurpose>get DSA signature size</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>#include &lt;openssl/dsa.h&gt;</synopsis>
<synopsis>int DSA_size(const DSA *dsa);</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection xml:id="ID-d75e898653840d3b9d6d9e215c3a4ae2"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      This function returns the size of an ASN.1 encoded DSA signature in
      bytes. It can be used to determine how much memory must be allocated
      for a DSA signature.
    </para>
    <para>
      <emphasis role="bold">dsa-&gt;q</emphasis> must not be <emphasis role="bold">NULL</emphasis>.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection xml:id="ID-7a60fcf7e107ce7edfcce195aab5b747"><title>RETURN VALUE</title>
    <para>
      The size in bytes.
    </para>
  </refsection>
